    },
    {
      "index": 4,
      "start_time": 15220.0,
      "end_time": 17490.0,
      "text": "what they look like, and how they interconnect."
    },
    {
      "index": 5,
      "start_time": 17490.0,
      "end_time": 19850.0,
      "text": "Why are financial statements necessary?"
    },
    {
      "index": 6,
      "start_time": 19850.0,
      "end_time": 22540.0,
      "text": "Remember that external users, mainly investors, lenders,"
    },
    {
      "index": 7,
      "start_time": 22540.0,
      "end_time": 24610.0,
      "text": "and other creditors, have to make decisions"
    },
    {
      "index": 8,
      "start_time": 24610.0,
      "end_time": 27910.0,
      "text": "about resource allocations, where to put their money."
    },
    {
      "index": 9,
      "start_time": 27910.0,
      "end_time": 30100.0,
      "text": "They use financial statements to answer questions"
    },
    {
      "index": 10,
      "start_time": 30100.0,
      "end_time": 32200.0,
      "text": "that they may have about a business."
    },
    {
      "index": 11,
      "start_time": 32200.000000000004,
      "end_time": 34270.0,
      "text": "From the video on business organizations,"
    },
    {
      "index": 12,
      "start_time": 34270.0,
      "end_time": 37690.0,
      "text": "we know that corporations can be either public or private."
    },
    {
      "index": 13,
      "start_time": 37690.0,
      "end_time": 41530.0,
      "text": "Public corporations must follow IFRS, International Financial"
    },
    {
      "index": 14,
      "start_time": 41530.0,
      "end_time": 43180.0,
      "text": "Reporting Standards."
    },
    {
      "index": 15,
      "start_time": 43180.0,
      "end_time": 47410.0,
      "text": "Private corporations can follow either IFRS or ASPE, Accounting"
    },
    {
      "index": 16,
      "start_time": 47410.0,
      "end_time": 49960.0,
      "text": "Standards for Private Enterprises."
    },
    {
      "index": 17,
      "start_time": 49960.0,
      "end_time": 53170.0,
      "text": "Corporations who follow IFRS, whether public or private,"
    },
    {
      "index": 18,
      "start_time": 53170.0,
      "end_time": 55780.0,
      "text": "must produce the following financial statements--"
    },
    {
      "index": 19,
      "start_time": 55780.0,
      "end_time": 58570.0,
      "text": "the income statement, statement of comprehensive income,"
    },
    {
      "index": 20,
      "start_time": 58570.0,
      "end_time": 60520.0,
      "text": "statement of changes in equity, statement"
    },
    {
      "index": 21,
      "start_time": 60520.0,
      "end_time": 63290.0,
      "text": "of financial position, and finally, a statement of cash"
    },
    {
      "index": 22,
      "start_time": 63290.0,
      "end_time": 64239.0,
      "text": "flow."
    },
    {
      "index": 23,
      "start_time": 64239.00000000001,
      "end_time": 66070.0,
      "text": "A private company who follows ASPE"
    },
    {
      "index": 24,
      "start_time": 66070.0,
      "end_time": 68170.0,
      "text": "produces slightly different statements--"
    },
    {
      "index": 25,
      "start_time": 68170.0,
      "end_time": 71260.0,
      "text": "an income statement, statement of retained earnings, balance"
    },
    {
      "index": 26,
      "start_time": 71260.0,
      "end_time": 73327.0,
      "text": "sheet, and a cash flow statement."
    },
    {
      "index": 27,
      "start_time": 73327.0,
      "end_time": 75160.0,
      "text": "If you wish to learn about these statements,"
    },
    {
      "index": 28,
      "start_time": 75160.0,
      "end_time": 78540.0,
      "text": "go to my video on ASPE financial statements."
    },
    {
      "index": 29,
      "start_time": 78540.0,
      "end_time": 81190.0,
      "text": "IFRS required financial statements must be completed"
    },
    {
      "index": 30,
      "start_time": 81190.0,
      "end_time": 82870.0,
      "text": "in a specific order, and we&#39;ll start"
    },
    {
      "index": 31,
      "start_time": 82870.0,
      "end_time": 85060.0,
      "text": "with the income statement."
    },
    {
      "index": 32,
      "start_time": 85060.0,
      "end_time": 87310.0,
      "text": "An income statement reports the results of a company&#39;s"
    },
    {
      "index": 33,
      "start_time": 87310.0,
      "end_time": 89050.0,
      "text": "day-to-day operation."
    },
    {
      "index": 34,
      "start_time": 89050.0,
      "end_time": 91780.0,
      "text": "It reports the revenues, less the expenses incurred"
    },
    {
      "index": 35,
      "start_time": 91780.0,
      "end_time": 95759.0,
      "text": "to generate that revenue, to obtain a profit or loss figure."
    },
    {
      "index": 36,
      "start_time": 95759.0,
      "end_time": 98050.0,
      "text": "The income statement measures the company&#39;s performance"
    },
    {
      "index": 37,
      "start_time": 98050.0,
      "end_time": 101170.0,
      "text": "within a period of time, either annually, quarterly,"
    },
    {
      "index": 38,
      "start_time": 101170.0,
      "end_time": 102210.0,
      "text": "or monthly."
    },
    {
      "index": 39,
      "start_time": 102210.0,
      "end_time": 103960.0,
      "text": "To better understand the income statement,"
    },
    {
      "index": 40,
      "start_time": 103960.0,
      "end_time": 107080.0,
      "text": "we have to understand the two main elements, revenues"
    },
    {
      "index": 41,
      "start_time": 107080.0,
      "end_time": 108550.0,
      "text": "and expenses."
    },
    {
      "index": 42,
      "start_time": 108550.0,
      "end_time": 111970.0,
      "text": "Revenues are an increase in assets, either cash or accounts"
    },
    {
      "index": 43,
      "start_time": 111970.0,
      "end_time": 115570.0,
      "text": "receivable, from selling a product or providing a service."
    },
    {
      "index": 44,
      "start_time": 115570.0,
      "end_time": 118240.0,
      "text": "Other forms of revenue are interest income, royalty"
    },
    {
      "index": 45,
      "start_time": 118240.0,
      "end_time": 120580.0,
      "text": "income, or rental income."
    },
    {
      "index": 46,
      "start_time": 120580.0,
      "end_time": 122320.0,
      "text": "Expenses are the cost of anything"
    },
    {
      "index": 47,
      "start_time": 122320.0,
      "end_time": 125320.0,
      "text": "which is consumed, used, or incurred to help earn revenue"
    },
    {
      "index": 48,
      "start_time": 125320.0,
      "end_time": 127180.0,
      "text": "during that period of time."
    },
    {
      "index": 49,
      "start_time": 127180.0,
      "end_time": 130690.0,
      "text": "Common expenses are salaries, advertising, depreciation,"
    },
    {
      "index": 50,
      "start_time": 130690.0,
      "end_time": 134170.0,
      "text": "utilities, interest, and income tax expense."
    },
    {
      "index": 51,
      "start_time": 134170.0,
      "end_time": 136395.0,
      "text": "The format of an income statement is important."
    },
    {
      "index": 52,
      "start_time": 136395.0,
      "end_time": 137770.0,
      "text": "Note that the heading must always"
    },
    {
      "index": 53,
      "start_time": 137770.0,
      "end_time": 139570.0,
      "text": "include the company name, the title"
    },
    {
      "index": 54,
      "start_time": 139570.0,
      "end_time": 142270.0,
      "text": "of the financial statement, and the time period covered."
    },
    {
      "index": 55,
      "start_time": 142270.0,
      "end_time": 143872.0,
      "text": "Revenues are listed first."
    },
    {
      "index": 56,
      "start_time": 143872.0,
      "end_time": 145330.0,
      "text": "If there are multiple revenues, you"
    },
    {
      "index": 57,
      "start_time": 145330.0,
      "end_time": 147310.0,
      "text": "must list each different type of revenue"
    },
    {
      "index": 58,
      "start_time": 147310.0,
      "end_time": 150790.0,
      "text": "individually and then show a subtotal called total revenues."
    },
    {
      "index": 59,
      "start_time": 150790.0,
      "end_time": 154120.0,
      "text": "Expenses are listed next, with a total of all expenses."
    },
    {
      "index": 60,
      "start_time": 154120.0,
      "end_time": 156910.0,
      "text": "There is a profit before income tax expense, then"
    },
    {
      "index": 61,
      "start_time": 156910.0,
      "end_time": 159460.0,
      "text": "income tax expense as a separate line item,"
    },
    {
      "index": 62,
      "start_time": 159460.0,
      "end_time": 161920.0,
      "text": "before listing a final profit amount."
    },
    {
      "index": 63,
      "start_time": 161920.0,
      "end_time": 164350.0,
      "text": "Note that if expenses are greater than revenues,"
    },
    {
      "index": 64,
      "start_time": 164350.0,
      "end_time": 167530.0,
      "text": "a loss amount is provided at the bottom of the statement."
    },
    {
      "index": 65,
      "start_time": 167530.0,
      "end_time": 170274.0,
      "text": "This is called a single step income statement."
    },
    {
      "index": 66,
      "start_time": 170274.0,
      "end_time": 171940.0,
      "text": "We&#39;ll be covering a multiple step income"
    },
    {
      "index": 67,
      "start_time": 171940.0,
      "end_time": 174630.0,
      "text": "statement in a future video."
    },
    {
      "index": 68,
      "start_time": 174630.0,
      "end_time": 176550.0,
      "text": "Remember to pause the video to determine"
    },
    {
      "index": 69,
      "start_time": 176550.0,
      "end_time": 178440.0,
      "text": "your answer to this check your understanding"
    },
    {
      "index": 70,
      "start_time": 178440.0,
      "end_time": 181980.0,
      "text": "question about the uses of the income statement."
    },
    {
      "index": 71,
      "start_time": 181980.0,
      "end_time": 184740.0,
      "text": "Investors are interested in a company&#39;s past performance"
    },
    {
      "index": 72,
      "start_time": 184740.0,
      "end_time": 186041.0,
      "text": "because it helps them--"
    },
    {
      "index": 73,
      "start_time": 190330.0,
      "end_time": 192990.0,
      "text": "the answer is not A. Determining the amount of debt"
    },
    {
      "index": 74,
      "start_time": 192990.0,
      "end_time": 194790.0,
      "text": "a company currently has is answered"
    },
    {
      "index": 75,
      "start_time": 194790.0,
      "end_time": 197740.0,
      "text": "by reviewing the statement of financial position."
    },
    {
      "index": 76,
      "start_time": 197740.0,
      "end_time": 200760.0,
      "text": "The answer is not B, as the current value of a company&#39;s"
    },
    {
      "index": 77,
      "start_time": 200760.0,
      "end_time": 202387.0,
      "text": "property, plant, and equipment is only"
    },
    {
      "index": 78,
      "start_time": 202387.0,
      "end_time": 203970.0,
      "text": "on the statement of financial position"
    },
    {
      "index": 79,
      "start_time": 203970.0,
      "end_time": 206730.0,
      "text": "if the company chooses to use fair value."
    },
    {
      "index": 80,
      "start_time": 206730.0,
      "end_time": 208620.0,
      "text": "The answer is not D either."
    },
    {
      "index": 81,
      "start_time": 208620.0,
      "end_time": 210660.0,
      "text": "Determining if a company is profitable enough"
    },
    {
      "index": 82,
      "start_time": 210660.0,
      "end_time": 212790.0,
      "text": "to repay its debt is what lenders will"
    },
    {
      "index": 83,
      "start_time": 212790.0,
      "end_time": 214620.0,
      "text": "use the income statement for."
    },
    {
      "index": 84,
      "start_time": 214620.0,
      "end_time": 216780.0,
      "text": "The correct answer is C, as investors"
    },
    {
      "index": 85,
      "start_time": 216780.0,
      "end_time": 219420.0,
      "text": "are interested in determining the future profitability"
    },
    {
      "index": 86,
      "start_time": 219420.0,
      "end_time": 220800.0,
      "text": "of a company."
    },
    {
      "index": 87,
      "start_time": 220800.0,
      "end_time": 222480.0,
      "text": "Why is this?"
    },
    {
      "index": 88,
      "start_time": 222480.0,
      "end_time": 224310.0,
      "text": "Because it will help investors determine"
    },
    {
      "index": 89,
      "start_time": 224310.0,
      "end_time": 227520.0,
      "text": "if they should keep or sell the shares they own in the company."
    },
    {
      "index": 90,
      "start_time": 227520.0,
      "end_time": 229230.0,
      "text": "Investors also use the income statement"
    },
    {
      "index": 91,
      "start_time": 229230.0,
      "end_time": 230880.0,
      "text": "to determine if the company will be"
    },
    {
      "index": 92,
      "start_time": 230880.0,
      "end_time": 232759.0,
      "text": "in a position to pay dividends."
    },
    {
      "index": 93,
      "start_time": 232759.0,
      "end_time": 235050.0,
      "text": "Lenders use the income statement to help them determine"
    },
    {
      "index": 94,
      "start_time": 235050.0,
      "end_time": 237360.0,
      "text": "if they can fund the company with loans"
    },
    {
      "index": 95,
      "start_time": 237360.0,
      "end_time": 239970.0,
      "text": "and if the company will be in a position to repay the loan"
    },
    {
      "index": 96,
      "start_time": 239970.0,
      "end_time": 242130.0,
      "text": "plus interest in the future."
    },
    {
      "index": 97,
      "start_time": 242130.0,
      "end_time": 243600.0,
      "text": "Other creditors use this statement"
    },
    {
      "index": 98,
      "start_time": 243600.0,
      "end_time": 245850.0,
      "text": "to figure out if the company will be profitable enough"
    },
    {
      "index": 99,
      "start_time": 245850.0,
      "end_time": 248550.0,
      "text": "to repay their debts as they come due."
    },
    {
      "index": 100,
      "start_time": 248550.0,
      "end_time": 251010.0,
      "text": "The long-term survival of any corporation"
    },
    {
      "index": 101,
      "start_time": 251010.0,
      "end_time": 253530.0,
      "text": "depends on its ability to produce revenues that are"
    },
    {
      "index": 102,
      "start_time": 253530.0,
      "end_time": 255420.0,
      "text": "greater than their expenses."
    },
    {
      "index": 103,
      "start_time": 255420.0,
      "end_time": 258089.0,
      "text": "Profits allow a company to fund their financing activities"
    },
    {
      "index": 104,
      "start_time": 258089.0,
      "end_time": 260190.0,
      "text": "by paying dividends to shareholders and interest"
    },
    {
      "index": 105,
      "start_time": 260190.0,
      "end_time": 261390.0,
      "text": "to lenders."
    },
    {
      "index": 106,
      "start_time": 261390.0,
      "end_time": 264030.0,
      "text": "It also allows a company to pay for investing activities,"
    },
    {
      "index": 107,
      "start_time": 264030.0,
      "end_time": 265770.0,
      "text": "like buying new equipment."
    },
    {
      "index": 108,
      "start_time": 265770.0,
      "end_time": 268680.0,
      "text": "Investors buy and sell shares, and creditors loan money,"
    },
    {
      "index": 109,
      "start_time": 268680.0,
      "end_time": 272250.0,
      "text": "based on their beliefs about a company&#39;s future performance."
    },
    {
      "index": 110,
      "start_time": 272250.0,
      "end_time": 274830.0,
      "text": "Income statements, which show past performance,"
    },
    {
      "index": 111,
      "start_time": 274830.0,
      "end_time": 279042.0,
      "text": "give users information to help predict future performance."
    },
    {
      "index": 112,
      "start_time": 279042.0,
      "end_time": 280500.0,
      "text": "The income statement is a statement"
    },
    {
      "index": 113,
      "start_time": 280500.0,
      "end_time": 283350.0,
      "text": "that is connected to many other financial statements."
    },
    {
      "index": 114,
      "start_time": 283350.0,
      "end_time": 285360.0,
      "text": "The profit or loss from the income statement"
    },
    {
      "index": 115,
      "start_time": 285360.0,
      "end_time": 287220.0,
      "text": "is the opening number for both the statement"
    },
    {
      "index": 116,
      "start_time": 287220.0,
      "end_time": 289980.0,
      "text": "of comprehensive income and the statement of cash flows,"
    },
    {
      "index": 117,
      "start_time": 289980.0,
      "end_time": 291810.0,
      "text": "under the indirect method."
    },
    {
      "index": 118,
      "start_time": 291810.0,
      "end_time": 293760.0,
      "text": "In addition, profit is carried forward"
    },
    {
      "index": 119,
      "start_time": 293760.0,
      "end_time": 295440.0,
      "text": "to the statement of changes in equity,"
    },
    {
      "index": 120,
      "start_time": 295440.0,
      "end_time": 297860.0,
      "text": "under the retained earnings column."
    },
    {
      "index": 121,
      "start_time": 297860.0,
      "end_time": 299610.0,
      "text": "Since the profit from the income statement"
    },
    {
      "index": 122,
      "start_time": 299610.0,
      "end_time": 301800.0,
      "text": "is used in other statements, it is always"
    },
    {
      "index": 123,
      "start_time": 301800.0,
      "end_time": 303960.0,
      "text": "the first financial statement completed."
    },
    {
      "index": 124,
      "start_time": 303960.0,
      "end_time": 306420.0,
      "text": "The next statement produced is the statement"
    },
    {
      "index": 125,
      "start_time": 306420.0,
      "end_time": 308160.0,
      "text": "of comprehensive income, which we&#39;ll"
    },
    {
      "index": 126,
      "start_time": 308160.0,
      "end_time": 310790.0,
      "text": "be covering in the next video."
    }
  ]
}